Description: ChEMBL is a database of bioactive drug-like small molecules- it contains 2-D structures- calculated properties (e.g. logP- Molecular Weight- Lipinski Parameters- etc.) and abstracted bioactivities (e.g. binding constants- pharmacology and ADMET data). The data is abstracted and curated from the primary scientific literature- and cover a significant fraction of the SAR and discovery of modern drugs.It is available in RDF form through EMBL-EBI's RDF Platform.
